The tiny Humboldt County town of Bridgeville welcomes aliens and...
Bigfoot isn’t the only mysterious creature found in redwood country. Mid-August brings all sorts of extraterrestrials and spacey humanoids to the galaxy-famous Flying Saucer Trials during the annual Bridgefest, gathering on the bridge 45 feet above the Van Duzen River in Bridgeville, a town once put up for sale on eBay. The contest of precision, distance and style is open to all comers who show up with a homemade craft, as are more grounded diversions, such as barbecue and blueberry pie, arts and crafts displays, live music and the new, ever-so-earthy Dirtbag Muster obstacle course.
